POVsync — third-party components
================================

POVsync itself is licensed under the MIT License (see LICENSE).

The POVsync application invokes the tools below as **separate executables** (via
child-process calls), and the Windows installer redistributes verified copies of them.
Each retains its own license; bundling them does not change POVsync's own MIT license.


yt-dlp
------
  Role:    media discovery and sliced downloading
  License: The Unlicense (public domain)
  Source:  https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp
  The yt-dlp binary is fetched and SHA-256-verified at package time (build/fetch-tools.mjs).


FFmpeg
------
  Role:    trimming and remuxing downloaded segments
  License: GNU General Public License v3 (the bundled build is a GPL build)
  Source:  https://ffmpeg.org  ·  Windows build: https://www.gyan.dev/ffmpeg/builds/
  The complete corresponding source for FFmpeg is available from the FFmpeg project and
  from the build provider above. The FFmpeg binary is fetched and SHA-256-verified at
  package time and is invoked as a standalone executable; it is not linked into POVsync.


Electron
--------
  Role:    desktop application shell
  License: MIT
  Source:  https://github.com/electron/electron


Other dependencies
------------------
  POVsync's renderer and engine use open-source npm packages (React, Vite, TailwindCSS,
  framer-motion, lucide-react, zod, esbuild, tsx, and others), each under its own
  permissive license (MIT / ISC / Apache-2.0). See each package's entry in node_modules
  for its full license text.
